Ah, damn it... My back hurts... How heavy was that
old man...\n< Cecilia >

But well, we won't be found for a while now. The
kids are trained not to enter rooms on their own.\n< Cecilia >
How are your injuries?\n< Cecilia >
Somehow... The swelling on my face has gone down.\n< Serena >
That's good then...\n< Cecilia >
...\n< Serena >

You look down. But then again, you were just
raped, so it's not like you could be cheerful.\n< Cecilia >
...That's part of it...\n< Serena >
What, are you worried about the guy who died? Ha.\n< Cecilia >

Listen, like I said before, you don't need to
worry about anything. That guy deserved to die,
and that's why I killed him.\n< Cecilia >
You just happened to be there at that time.\n< Cecilia >
...Yes...\n< Serena >
Phew...\n< Cecilia >
Thanks for everything.\n< Cecilia >
Yes...\n< Serena >

...I'll say it again, you don't need to worry
about anything.\n< Cecilia >

He lived his life in a way that he deserved to be
stabbed from behind. He was careless today and
died. I killed him.\n< Cecilia >
You just happened to be there at that time.\n< Cecilia >
...Yes...\n< Serena >
Ha-...\n< Cecilia >

Alright, alright. Anyway, this matter is now in my
hands. It's over. Move on. End of discussion.\n< Cecilia >
Let's talk about what comes next.\n< Cecilia >
What comes next?\n< Serena >

Yes. I owe you... Serena, a huge debt of
gratitude.\n< Cecilia >
So now it's my turn.\n< Cecilia >

I'll help save Unicorn-chan. That plan we talked
about, I'm going to seriously get involved.\n< Cecilia >
That is... appreciated but...\n< Serena >
That is... sincerely appreciated.\n< Serena >

Especially now, in this situation. If used well,
we can greatly improve the precision of the plan.\n< Cecilia >

Just need some time to confirm things and organize
what needs to be done.\n< Cecilia >

I know Serena is in a hurry. So just give me one
night. I'll put together a plan in one night.\n< Cecilia >

Come to the orphanage when the sun rises tomorrow.
There, I'll discuss the plan with Serena.\n< Cecilia >

You also need time to rest your body, switch
gears, and calm down. Right now.\n< Cecilia >
...Yes...\n< Serena >
Understood.\n< Serena >

Oh, and this. Here's the money from earlier, 10000
S.\n< Cecilia >
Ah...\n< Serena >

You're not planning to stay here, right? Use it
for lodging or something.\n< Cecilia >
I will do that...\n< Serena >
I will do that.\n< Serena >

I think you understand, but the kids outside still
don't know what happened here.\n< Cecilia >

Make sure you leave naturally without arousing
suspicion. If the situation here leaks out, our
plan will be ruined.\n< Cecilia >
I have taken note.\n< Serena >
Then, until tomorrow.\n< Serena >
Yes, until tomorrow.\n< Cecilia >
...Ah...uh...it hurts...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

...Fear, pain, sin, and confusion. I'll leave it
all behind tonight.\n< Serena >

Finally, finally a path has opened up. Now is not
the time to falter...\n< Serena >
...It's completely night now.\n< Serena >

...Come to think of it, this might be the first
night I've spent in this town without following
anyone's orders.\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

...It's a bit chilly. I should find a place to
stay quickly.\n< Serena >
